&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are currently seeking an enthusiastic and motivated Apprentice to work within our busy administration department within Women&#39;s Services. This is a perfect opportunity to develop your administration skills whilst gaining a qualification. Please refer to the job description for more detail.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hours of work will be 35 across Monday to Friday – it is expected that there will be some flexibility in how these are worked, allowing time within the week for Apprenticeship study.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please read the person specification before applying for this Apprentice post to ensure that you meet the required criteria.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
